added.title: I Am My Mom
added.description: Steven struggles to fix his mistakes.

added.title: Drop Beat Dad
added.description: Steven helps Sour Cream put on a show, even though Sour Cream's stepdad doesn't approve of DJs.

added.title: Too Far
added.description: Amethyst and Steven get in on some Gem gossip.

added.title: The Shippening
added.description: When people that barely know each other start falling in love, Gumball thinks he knows who's behind it. He rushes to Sarah's house and finds her writing in a magic notebook that turns everything in it into reality. When everything in Elmore gets crazier and crazier there's only one thing for it: they have to write their way out.

added.title: The Spinoffs
added.description: Wishing to get rid of Gumball once and for all, his nemesis Rob offers up a variety of reality, action and comedy shows featuring characters other than Gumball. Unfortunately for Rob each one is worse than the last…

added.title: The Pizza
added.description: The Wattersons have had a bad day, but it turns out Larry has too and it's about to get worse . . . for everyone! The Wattersons complain about their day and order a pizza from Larry. When they call to complain about their late pizza it's the final straw for Larry and he quits all of his jobs. Elmore's fragile commercial structure collapses and the citizens revert to a more primitive apocalyptic state.

added.title: The Prank
added.description: Gumball and Darwin's harmless pranks on Dad spiral hopelessly out of control.

added.title: Growing Pains
added.description: Puppycorn is sick of Unikitty always helping him out and doesn't want to be the "little" brother anymore, so he uses some of Dr Fox's 'grow taffy' to grow literally bigger than Unikitty. Meanwhile, a black hole is on its way to destroy the planet. But when Puppycorn takes too much and continues growing, he starts accidentally destroying the kingdom. Unikitty takes grow taffy and grows big as well to help out, but when they're both the size of planets, Puppycorn proves he can take care of himself on his own by destroying the black hole and saving the kingdom.

added.title: Wiener Club
added.description: Puppycorn is determined to become the Hot Dog King and joins an underground hot dog eating contest called Weiner Club. Rick warns "you are what you eat," but Puppycorn doesn't listen and eats so many hot dogs he becomes the new champion of Weiner Club. Unfortunately he also literally turns into a hot dog, that the other club members reveal they are going to eat! Unikitty and the gang now must attack with vegetables and defeat the hot dog-eating baddies in order to save the giant hot-dog-shaped Puppycorn and turn him back to normal.

added.title: Trapped in the Tower
added.description: During a fun fireworks show, Unikitty and Master Frown become trapped in the horn of the Unikitty Castle when she catches Master Frown messing with her fireworks. Unikitty takes this as an opportunity to figure out why Master Frown is always such a Cranky McCrabby Face all the time, if only Master Frown would let his emotional guard down! She tries all kinds of tactics, a song, a dance, even a firework with a face drawn on it named "Professor Pow Pow, licensed therapist" Getting nowhere, Unikitty ends up raging out and setting the tower and all the fireworks alight. In desperation to not burn alive, Master Frown tells Unikitty a story about a younger Master Frown who was gifted a special lollipop but after a freak chain of events, was broken right before his eyes. Unikitty cries her eyes out and puts out the fires and then reveals it was her plan all along to get Master Frown to talk about his feelings!

added.title: Special Delivery
added.description: After being rudely interrupted by Bim Bom during her daily morning song, an angry Unikitty takes the advice of her friends and writes down her feelings into a letter with the intention of keeping the letter to herself, but then accidentally sends it off, complete with postage! The gang then goes on a wild chase through the Unikingdom mail delivery service to keep that rude letter from getting into the hands of Bim Bom, and ultimately hurting her feelings. Turns out, Unikitty's "rude" is everyone else's "nice" and the letter was full of compliments.

added.title: Scary Tales 2
added.description: It's Halloween again and the gang is desperately trying to tell the scariest story to a couple of trick or treaters. Each of the characters takes turns adding onto the last story, going through a haunted glove to a haunted action figure to haunted everything, and even a spooky song! None work in scaring the kids when suddenly a full scale alien invasion happens right before their eyes! Still, the trick or treaters are unimpressed until Richard takes the story stage and delivers a story no kid wants to hear- instead of candy, the trick or treaters would get granola bars! The kids, and Puppycorn, run away screaming.

added.title: Attack of Thermometron 9000
added.description: Axel must wrangle Galileo and Bobbie to shut down a rogue thermostat - improperly upgraded by Slobot - as it plunges the house into extreme hot and cold zones.

added.title: Access Denied
added.description: When Axel and the team try to figure out what Sarge Charge's secret weapon is, they get ejected from the house by his newly upgraded security system and must fight their way back inside before Madcap does.

added.title: Swing Set Jet Set
added.description: Axel and the team battle Princess SugarSalt for possession of Bearbarian's hammer, traded to her by one of their own - Galileo!

added.title: All Trick No Treat
added.description: On Halloween, Axel gets too caught up in the scares and loses track of the fun - just in time for an infiltration by the worst trick 'r' treater of all, Madcap!

added.title: Gathering Dark
added.description: Axel must help Bearbarian overcome his secret fear of the dark to stop Dynamo from stealing his ride.

added.title: Boxman Crashes
added.description: Lord Boxman crashes at Venomous' lair and inserts himself into his villainous affairs.

added.title: Sidekick Scouts
added.description: KO gets more than he bargained for when he gets a sidekick.

added.title: Stop Attacking the Plaza
added.description: Boxman must go 24 hours without attacking Lakewood Plaza Turbo.

added.title: No More Pow Cards
added.description: When KO realizes Pow Cards exclude his friend, he's at a loss of what to do.

added.title: Rad Likes Robots
added.description: Rad finds love in an unexpected place.

added.title: Perfect Day
added.description: Ben thinks he's having 'the perfect day' only to realize he's been put in a dream world by Enoch and the Forever Knights who are after the Omnitrix. Ben's "dream world" soon becomes a nightmare world, with Ben forced to live out his ultimate terror...being stuck at school! But with Max and Gwen's help, he's able to vanquish his nightmare foes and re-enter the real world where he takes down  Enoch...only to reveal an even more powerful knight...The Forever King.

added.title: Big Fat Alien Wedding
added.description: Ben and Gwen accompany Max to a wedding, which doesn't make Ben particularly happy, especially given the fact he has to wear a tux and learn how to dance. During the wedding it's revealed that the bride's parents are aliens while the groom's family are ex-Plumbers. It turns out the bride's parents are out to sabotage the wedding because of a long lasting feud with the Plumbers, and take action by demonstrating their destructive powers and causing deadly havoc. Ben, Max and Gwen enter the fray and not only save the day, but make sure the ceremony goes on as planned.

added.title: Morituri Te Salutamus
added.description: Finn and Jake are trapped in the arena of the Fight King and must face gladiators to set themselves free.

added.title: Plane Excited
added.description: Clarence is all excited visit his grandma when he learns that Chad has never been on a plane. Clarence makes it his mission to help Chad get through a hectic flight.

added.title: Summer Bummer
added.description: When the beach is taken over by the most excellent Bro Sharks, will the Girls be gnarly enough to save the day?

added.title: Hundred Dollar Gus
added.description: Pizza Steve makes up a preposterous lie that lands the gang in big trouble.

added.title: Mortal Recoil
added.description: Mortal Recoil: Doctor Ice Cream brings PB back from the brink of death, but is she really herself?

added.title: Space Race
added.description: With Clarence distracted by the mysterious power of the moon, his class competes to build the highest-flying rocket. Will Sumo's homemade bucket of bolts beat Belson's store-bought rocket?

added.title: Perfect Storm Part 1
added.description: Arcee and Grimlock go off on an adventure only to return and discover the Ark without power and their friends all in stand-by mode.

added.title: Perfect Storm Part 2
added.description: Arcee and Grimlock get an adventure they never bargained for as they protect the helpless Ark from all manner of space anomalies.

added.title: Dollar Hunt
added.description: Clarence hosts a fun "dollar hunt" game to meet new friends. But things go awry when Clarence accidentally buries the money his Mom gave him to buy refreshments for her book club meeting.

added.title: Tiara Trouble
added.description: Bubbles' excitement over being a contestant in the Townsville Beauty, Talent and All-Around Flair pageant is ruined when Blossom and Buttercup become overbearing stage-sisters. But when a mysterious tiara causes trouble for the contestants, they realize there are bigger problems at hand.

added.title: Dog Day
added.description: When a father refuses his daughter's request for a dog, Uncle Grandpa vows to teach the girl responsibility by becoming a dog.

added.title: Where the Wild Chads Are
added.description: Chad takes Clarence out to the woods for some grizzly-man camping but Clarence is disappointed at the cushy set up; heaters, a hammock, even a portable TV. To make it a more rugged adventure, Clarence ditches Chad's wallet, cell phone and all their food but it may be too much wilderness for them to handle.

added.title: The Vampire Strikes Back
added.description: Ben, Rook, and Rad Dudesman come face to face with the evil Lord Transyl, a vampire-like alien who can make anyone his loyal slave! (Introducing new Ben alien, Whampire.)

added.title: And Then There Was Ben
added.description: Professor Paradox unites the good Bens from across all dimensions to take on Vilgax, Eon, and the evil Bens in the ultimate showdown!

added.title: The Vengers
added.description: Billy Billions, Kangaroo Kommando, and Captain Nemesis team up to take down Ben, and claim his place as protector of Bellwood?!?

added.title: No Honor Among Bros
added.description: Rook is under the influence of Fistrick's "bro" essence, and starts to act like a bro. Can he and Ben infiltrate an alien fight club to claim the Golden Fist? (Introducing Slix Vigma, alien promoter.)

added.title: Clyde Five
added.description: Ben's country cousin wants to be a hero, too.
